    "description": "Grants focus on improving the well-being of nonhuman animals in areas such as neglected geographic regions, research into animal advocacy or welfare, activities facilitating future aid, and exceptional opportunities. Options for funding include supporting farmed animal advocacy in Asia, fish welfare research, alternative protein promotion, and anti-cruelty agriculture practices. The Animal Welfare Fund intends to support projects that direct welfare improvements mainly for farmed animals. Grants have funded activities like developing the US tofu market, influencing animal welfare policies in Brazilian public purchases, and expanding animal welfare work in India. The fund supports various efforts like research for advocacy effectiveness, corporate policy reform campaigns, and advocacy for alternative proteins.",
